problem_text:
A university has the following enrollment data:

- Set P (Philosophy students): {Mira, Neel, Omar, Priya, Qasim, Riya}
- Set M (Mathematics students): {Mira, Neel, Omar, Qasim, Sana}
- Set L (Logic course enrollees): {Mira, Neel, Omar, Priya, Tara}

An advisor claims: "Every student who is in both Philosophy and Mathematics is also enrolled in the Logic course."

Is this claim true based on the data?

In a student body:
- Set A = Students who play sports = {p, q, r, s, t}
- Set B = Students who are on the honor roll = {q, r, u, v}
- The policy states: "Students who play sports AND are NOT on the honor roll must attend study hall."

Which students must attend study hall?

